             depos'd, That he had frequently lost Coals, but was at a difficulty to know how, and therefore employ'd 4 Men to watch in a Yard were the Coals lay; the 2d Night between 1 and 2 o'Clock, 2 Men came to the Door, and he then heard the Padlock open, and next the Stock lock, and in came the Prisoner and a Brother of his, 
               <persName id="t17291203-9-person83">
                  George 
                  Bodington 
               <interp inst="t17291203-9-person83" type="surname" value="Bodington"></interp>
